<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Intuit (INTU)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Intuit Inc. — using actual financials, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${fy2025Rev !== null ? (fy2025Rev / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${fcfBase !== null ? (fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding : 'N/A'}M</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Shares Out</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Intuit generated <strong>${fcfBase !== null ? (fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'} billion</strong> in free cash flow over the trailing twelve months. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This growth rate is mathematically derived from Intuit's historical performance, moderated to a sustainable pace.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong> — roughly GDP growth plus modest pricing power. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This is calculated using the current 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) and an appropriate risk premium derived from broad market assumptions for INTU.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding : 'N/A'}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Based on historically derived revenue and FCF growth trajectories. Intuit has demonstrated strong pricing power and cross-selling capabilities within its software ecosystem (TurboTax, QuickBooks, Credit Karma, Mailchimp).
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived strictly from the 10Y Treasury (4.18%) and an equity risk premium markup. A {(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% discount rate reflects the relatively high stability and recurring nature of Intuit's software subscription revenues.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth plus slight pricing power. A company that grows slower than GDP in perpetuity eventually becomes irrelevant — {(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% implies Intuit maintains its market position indefinitely.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (TTM)</td>
          <td>${fcfBase !== null ? fcfBase.toLocaleString() : 'N/A'}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × {(1 + growthRateTerminal).toFixed(3)})</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ ({(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% − {(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%))</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
          <td>${netCash !== null ? netCash.toLocaleString() : 'N/A'}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Equity Value</td>
          <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
          <td>{sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString() : 'N/A'}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  {revenueHistory.length > 0 && (
    <>
      <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
      <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>
      <p>Before trusting a forward projection, look at where the company has been.</p>

      <h3>Revenue ($M)</h3>
      <div class="bar-chart">
        {revenueHistory.map(r => (
          <div class="bar-row">
            <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
            <div class="bar-track">
              <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${(r.value / fy2025Rev) * 100}%`}>
                ${r.value.toLocaleString()}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h3>Free Cash Flow ($M)</h3>
      <div class="bar-chart">
        {fcfHistory.map(r => (
          <div class="bar-row">
            <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
            <div class="bar-track">
              <div class="bar-fill fcf" style={`width: ${(r.value / (fcfBase || 1)) * 100}%`}>
                ${r.value.toLocaleString()}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h3>Margin Trends</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
              <th>Operating Margin</th>
              <th>Profit Margin</th>
              <th>FCF Margin</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {marginHistory.map(m => (
              <tr>
                <td>{m.year}</td>
                <td>{m.operating}%</td>
                <td>{m.profit}%</td>
                <td>{m.fcfMargin}%</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </>
  )}

  <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
  <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
  <p>Our base case uses {(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% growth and {(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% discount rate. Here's what the intrinsic value looks like under different assumptions.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="sensitivity-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
          {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
            <th class={Math.abs(g - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(1)}%</th>
          ))}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
          <tr>
            <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(1)}%</td>
            {row.values.map((v, i) => (
              <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                ${v}
              </td>
            ))}
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Risks & What the Model Misses</h2>
  <p>No model is complete. Here's what could swing Intuit's actual value:</p>

  <h3>Upside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pricing power:</strong> Intuit regularly raises prices on TurboTax and QuickBooks with very little churn.</li>
    <li><strong>AI Integration:</strong> "Intuit Assist" could drive higher ARPU (average revenue per user) and better retention.</li>
    <li><strong>Credit Karma:</strong> If macroeconomic conditions improve, consumer lending could rebound significantly.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>IRS Free File:</strong> Continued government push for free tax filing software could disrupt the core TurboTax consumer segment.</li>
    <li><strong>SMB Weakness:</strong> QuickBooks is tied to the health of small businesses. An extended recession would hurt subscriber growth.</li>
    <li><strong>Mailchimp integration:</strong> Slower than expected realization of synergies from the expensive Mailchimp acquisition.</li>
  </ul>

