      <summary>Why use DCF instead of a P/E multiple?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Multiples tell you what the market is paying, not what a company is worth. A DCF forces explicit assumptions about cash flows.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is this a buy recommendation?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">No. This is an analytical framework for estimating intrinsic value. Consult a financial advisor before investing.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

